diff --git a/gdverify/CMakeLists.txt b/gdverify/CMakeLists.txt
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..72d02d27dcd464e9bf6fed64f5c95b5453fcb80f
--- /dev/null
+++ b/gdverify/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@
+cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.16)
+project(gdverify)
+
+set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 17)
+set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD_REQUIRED ON)
+
+set(GODOT_SRC_DIR "${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/../godot" CACHE PATH "Path to Godot source")
+
+add_library(gdscript STATIC
+    ${GODOT_SRC_DIR}/modules/gdscript/gdscript_parser.cpp
+    ${GODOT_SRC_DIR}/modules/gdscript/gdscript_tokenizer.cpp
+    ${GODOT_SRC_DIR}/modules/gdscript/gdscript_tokenizer_buffer.cpp
+)
+
+target_include_directories(gdscript PUBLIC
+    ${GODOT_SRC_DIR}
+    ${GODOT_SRC_DIR}/platform/linuxbsd
+    ${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/include
+)
+
+target_compile_definitions(gdscript PUBLIC
+    TOOLS_ENABLED=0
+    DEBUG_ENABLED=0
+    UNIX_ENABLED=1
+)
+
+add_executable(gdverify src/main.cpp)
+target_include_directories(gdverify PUBLIC ${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/include ${GODOT_SRC_DIR})
+target_link_libraries(gdverify PRIVATE gdscript)
+target_compile_definitions(gdverify PRIVATE UNIX_ENABLED=1)
+
diff --git a/gdverify/README.md b/gdverify/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..b6a02cd19c54a973bde4e52493cb3b47bbf42a7a
--- /dev/null
+++ b/gdverify/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,24 @@
+# gdverify
+
+This utility builds a small parser from the Godot Engine sources and provides a command line tool to verify GDScript files.
+
+## Building
+
+```bash
+mkdir build && cd build
+cmake ../gdverify -DGODOT_SRC_DIR=../godot -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
+cmake --build . --parallel
+```
+
+## Usage
+
+```bash
+./gdverify <file.gd>
+```
+
+Return code `65` indicates a parse error.
+
+## Updating Godot Source
+
+To update the bundled Godot version, pull the latest release into the `godot/` directory (or update the submodule if used), then rebuild.
+Extend the shim headers in `gdverify/include` only if new missing symbols appear.

index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..7008fd8558f634697edda5ef01d8203602514e46
--- /dev/null
+++ b/gdverify/include/godot_defs.h
@@ -0,0 +1,16 @@
+#ifndef GDVERIFY_GODOT_DEFS_H
+#define GDVERIFY_GODOT_DEFS_H
+
+#include <cstdint>
+#include <cmath>
+
+// Maximum length of a token string for the tokenizer.
+#ifndef GDSCRIPT_TOKEN_MAX_LEN
+#define GDSCRIPT_TOKEN_MAX_LEN 256
+#endif
+
+namespace Math {
+inline bool is_power_of_two(uint64_t x) { return x && ((x & (x - 1)) == 0); }
+}
+
+#endif // GDVERIFY_GODOT_DEFS_H
diff --git a/gdverify/include/mini_godot_core.h b/gdverify/include/mini_godot_core.h
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..2c51bef90ee194ae52b821bc111037a0bc5e7748
--- /dev/null
+++ b/gdverify/include/mini_godot_core.h
@@ -0,0 +1,24 @@
+#ifndef MINI_GODOT_CORE_H
+#define MINI_GODOT_CORE_H
+
+#include <cstdio>
+#include <cstdlib>
+
+// Minimal replacements for Godot error macros used by the parser.
+#define ERR_FAIL_COND_MSG(cond, msg) \
+    do { if (cond) { std::fprintf(stderr, "Error: %s\n", msg); return; } } while(0)
+
+#define ERR_FAIL_V_MSG(cond, retval, msg) \
+    do { if (cond) { std::fprintf(stderr, "Error: %s\n", msg); return retval; } } while(0)
+
+#define ERR_FAIL_COND_V_MSG(cond, retval, msg) ERR_FAIL_V_MSG(cond, retval, msg)
+
+#define ERR_FAIL_NULL(ptr) \
+    do { if ((ptr) == nullptr) { std::fprintf(stderr, "Null pointer error\n"); return; } } while(0)
+
+#define ERR_FAIL_INDEX(idx, size) \
+    do { if ((idx) < 0 || (idx) >= (size)) { std::fprintf(stderr, "Index error\n"); return; } } while(0)
+
+#define ERR_PRINT(msg) std::fprintf(stderr, "%s\n", msg)
+
+#endif // MINI_GODOT_CORE_H
diff --git a/gdverify/src/main.cpp b/gdverify/src/main.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..6f317517d5618c461e639b49d6657f8a63ba7e3e
--- /dev/null
+++ b/gdverify/src/main.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@
+#include <fstream>
+#include <iostream>
+#include <sstream>
+#include "godot/modules/gdscript/gdscript_parser.h"
+#include "mini_godot_core.h"
+#include "godot_defs.h"
+
+int main(int argc, char **argv) {
+    if (argc < 2) {
+        std::cerr << "Usage: " << argv[0] << " <script.gd>\n";
+        return 1;
+    }
+    std::ifstream ifs(argv[1]);
+    if (!ifs) {
+        std::cerr << "Failed to open file: " << argv[1] << "\n";
+        return 1;
+    }
+    std::stringstream buffer;
+    buffer << ifs.rdbuf();
+    std::string source = buffer.str();
+
+    GDScriptParser parser;
+    Error err = parser.parse(String(source.c_str()), String(), false, true);
+    if (err != OK) {
+        return 65; // parse error
+    }
+    return 0;
+}
